  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In the wilderness,.... The wilderness of Judea, which was not a desert and uninhabited but had many cities and villages in it, those that follow: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Betharabah; the first of these seems to be in the borders of Judah and Benjamin, and so is ascribed to both; see Joshua 15:6, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Betharabah; the first of these seems to be in the borders of Judah and Benjamin, and so is ascribed to both; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 15:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Middin, and Secacah; of the two last we read nowhere else, only in Judges 5:10; what we translate \"ye that sit in judgment\", Kimchi interprets, \"ye that dwell by Middin\", and says it is the name of a place in Joshua, and mentions this passage. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Middin, and Secacah; of the two last we read nowhere else, only in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Judges 5:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; what we translate \"ye that sit in judgment\", Kimchi interprets, \"ye that dwell by Middin\", and says it is the name of a place in Joshua, and mentions this passage. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
